Package: SplicingGraphs
Title: Tools for creating splicing graphs from annotations and RNA-Seq data
Version: 0.6
Author: D. Bindreither, M. Carlson, M. Morgan, H. Pages
License: Artistic-2.0
Description: This package provides tools for creating splicing graphs based on
	transcript annotations and additionally tools for testing for
	differential splicing event usage based on genomic count data from
	RNA-seq experiments. 
Maintainer: H. Pages <hpages@fhcrc.org>
Depends: BiocGenerics, IRanges (>= 1.17.40), GenomicRanges,
	 Rgraphviz (>= 2.3.7), GenomicFeatures (>= 1.11.8), Rsamtools
Imports: methods, utils, igraph,
	 BiocGenerics, IRanges, GenomicRanges,
	 graph, Rgraphviz, GenomicFeatures, Rsamtools
Suggests: igraph, Gviz,
	 TxDb.Hsapiens.UCSC.hg19.knownGene,
	 TxDb.Mmusculus.UCSC.mm9.knownGene, TBX20BamSubset,
	 RUnit
Collate: igraph-utils.R
	 SplicingGraphs-class.R
	 sgedges-methods.R
	 sgraph-methods.R
	 bubbles-methods.R
	 countReads.R
	 toy_data.R
	 zzz.R
biocViews: Genetics, Annotation, HighThroughputSequencing
